## Usage

The sliding window is **automatic** and **transparent**:

```javascript
// User code remains the same
const entities = await nerLoader.predict(longText);

// Sliding window triggers automatically if text > 512 tokens
// User sees progress in console
// Returns merged, deduplicated entities
```

No API changes required!

---

## Summary

✅ **Handles documents of any length**
- No more truncation at 512 tokens
- 100% coverage of entire document

✅ **Maintains entity quality**
- Overlap prevents missed entities at boundaries
- Deduplication removes duplicates
- Confidence-based selection for duplicates

✅ **Transparent to user**
- Automatic detection of long documents
- Progress logging in console
- Same API as before

✅ **Efficient memory usage**
- Processes one chunk at a time
- No need to load entire document into GPU/model
- Suitable for very large documents (100K+ tokens)

⚠️ **Trade-off: Processing time**
- 22,553 tokens: ~25-30 seconds
- Acceptable for comprehensive PII detection
- Future optimizations possible (parallel, GPU)

